  "response_text": "The commercial begins with a flat cream-coloured title card reading “DULUTH TRADING” in large black block letters, with “DULUTHTRADING.COM” in red underneath. It then switches to a bright animated prehistoric landscape. A smoking volcano rises in the background under a blue sky, and a faint “InnoGames” logo sits at the upper right. In the foreground, a hairy bare arm lifts a large pale animal bone like a tool or club. The view widens to reveal a muscular, bearded caveman crouched on dusty ground beside a simple stone shelter made from large slabs, with an animal hide hanging at its entrance. He strikes or scrapes at small stones on the ground with the bone, sending bits of rock and dust outward.\n\nA prehistoric woman steps out from the stone shelter. She has very tall reddish-brown hair piled high on her head and wears a leopard-print, one-shouldered outfit with jewellery around her arm and neck. She pauses in front of the shelter, looking unimpressed, then plants her hands on her hips. The caveman turns toward her, looking uncertain and wide-eyed. A black lower-right banner appears with the white text “foe.tv.” He holds up the bone as if presenting an idea or tool. The bone is then shown close to a dark rock face, where it is used like a hammer against a small stone peg. The image transitions through time: the bone becomes a wooden mallet striking a post, and then a metal axe head drives into wood, visually suggesting tools advancing from primitive to more developed materials.\n\nThe setting changes to a sunny medieval village. A timber-and-stone house stands with a peaked roof, small window, and arched wooden door. A stocky worker in period clothing operates a rope and pulley beside it while the red-haired woman, now dressed in a fitted burgundy-and-white medieval-style gown with puffed sleeves and a black choker, stands in the right foreground watching. She smiles with satisfaction as the building work progresses behind her. The scene moves to a larger medieval construction area with a castle wall and tower in the background, half-timbered houses, scaffolding, and a wooden watchtower. A bearded man in a burgundy cap and vest stands at a worktable covered with small wooden blocks, parchment rolls, and tools. The red-haired woman stands just behind him. He raises a rectangular wooden block, then places it upright among the other blocks as if planning or building a model city.\n\nAs his hand sets the block down, the background shifts forward in time. Behind the tabletop model, modern glass skyscrapers begin to appear among the older buildings. One tall, sleek tower with a curved, sail-like shape rises prominently in the distance. The tabletop model remains made of simple wooden pieces, but the world behind it is becoming a contemporary city. The viewpoint pulls back above the table and surrounding cobblestone square, revealing the man seated or leaning at the worktable below. The view continues rising until a full city layout is visible: roads, green lawns, clusters of houses, futuristic towers, industrial-looking buildings, and decorative structures arranged like a strategy-game city map. The black “foe.tv” banner remains at the lower right.\n\nThe game city is then shown on a laptop screen, framed by a black bezel. The laptop displays the same top-down city with modern towers and roads. Other screens appear beside it: a tablet on the right shows a scenic medieval town with mountains in the background, and a smartphone in front displays the “Forge of Empires” logo on a shield and red banner. The devices sit on a tabletop, with the animated medieval village softly blurred behind them. Along the bottom, store badges appear, including “Download on the App Store,” “Get it on Google Play,” and an Amazon app-store badge, while “foe.tv” remains visible at the lower right.\n\nThe action returns to the animated world, now in a sleek futuristic office high above a city. Curved floor-to-ceiling windows look out over